    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Michigan</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The use of acupressure will be compared to targeted Raynaud's education and will evaluate
      the` frequency, duration and pain of Raynaud's attacks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Using a Raynaud's condition score, severity of tingling, numbness and pain of attacks, the
      number of attacks and patient and physician visual analog scale we will assess the effect of
      acupressure.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
